arrangementAttachments.fileName: Randwick Race Course Spring Carnival 19 September.pdf
arrangementAttachments.linkName: Randwick Race Day Special event clearways

properties.otherAdvice:
The Everest Carnival - George Main Stakes Day at Royal Randwick Racecourse from 12:15pm.

Motorists should allow extra travel time on Anzac Pde, Doncaster Ave, High St, Alison Rd and Darley Rd as large crowds travel to and from the racecourse.

Special event clearway parking restrictions will be in effect on roads around the racecourse including sections of Ascot St from 8am to 7pm and High St from 3pm to 7pm.

Clearways are strict no-parking zones, and apply even for local residents and RMS Mobility Scheme Permit holders. Check signs carefully as vehicles left in clearways will be towed and a fee applies.

arrangementElements.html:
RANDWICK 

FROM 8AM TO 7PM

  • Ascot St between Doncaster Ave and the roundabout at the racecourse (both sides)

FROM 3PM TO 7PM

  • High St between the gate 2 entry to UNSW and Anzac Pde (southern side)

properties.headline: NRL - Saturday 19 September - BROOKVALE Pittwater Road at Brookvale Oval
properties.otherAdvice:
NRL: Sea Eagles v Titans at Lottoland Brookvale Oval from 3pm until 5pm. 

Traffic may be heavier than usual on Pittwater Rd, Old Pittwater Rd, Warringah Rd and Beacon Hill Rd as fans travel to and from the stadium.

Fans driving to the game should allow extra travel time for parking and be aware of increased pedestrian activity on local roads.

properties.headline: NRL - Saturday 19 September - MOORE PARK Moore Park Rd, Anzac Pde, Lang Rd, Eastern Distributor approaching S.C.G.

arrangementAttachments.displayName: Moore Park walking & transport route map
arrangementAttachments.linkName: Moore Park walking & transport route map

properties.otherAdvice:
NRL: Roosters v Sharks at the SCG from 7:35pm until 9:35pm approx.

Traffic may be heavier than usual on Anzac Pde, Eastern Distributor, Moore Park Rd, Cleveland St and Lang Rd approaching Moore Park as fans travel to and from the game.

Driver Ave will also be partially closed from before the game and remain closed until crowds have safely cleared the precinct after full-time. 

Special event clearways will be in effect on various roads from 3pm until 11pm including sections of Moore Park Rd, Lang Rd, Chalmers St, Fitzroy St, Flinders St and Foveaux St.

Clearways are strict no-parking zones even for local residents and RMS Mobility Scheme Permit holders. Check signs carefully as vehicles left in clearways will be towed and a fee applies.

arrangementElements.html:
Special event clearways are strict no-parking zones even for local residents and RMS Mobility Scheme Parking Permit holders. Check signs carefully as vehicles left in clearways will be towed and a fee applies. If your vehicle is towed, call 132 701 to find its new location.

SURRY HILLS / MOORE PARK

FROM 6AM TO 11PM

  • Cleveland Street between City Road and South Dowling Street

FROM 3PM TO 11PM

  • Chalmers Street between Cleveland Street and Devonshire Street (western side)
  • Fitzroy Street between South Dowling Street and Bourke Street (northern side)
  • Flinders Street between Albion Street and Moore Park Road (eastern side)
  • Foveaux Street between Bourke Street and Crown Street (northern side)
  • Lang Road between Cook Road and Anzac Parade (both sides)
  • Moore Park Road between Driver Avenue and Anzac Parade (southern side)

properties.headline: NRL - Sunday 20 September - BROADMEADOW Griffiths Rd at Turton Rd
properties.publicTransport: Visit transportnsw.info to plan your trip.
properties.otherAdvice:
NRL: Knights v Dragons at McDonald Jones Stadium from 4:05pm until 6pm approx.

Traffic may be heavier than normal on Turton Rd, Griffiths Rd, Newcastle Rd, Lambton Rd and Bridges Rd through Broadmeadow as fans travel to and from the stadium.

Motorists should allow extra travel time and be aware of increased pedestrian activity on local roads.

properties.headline: NRL - Friday 18 September - PARRAMATTA O'Connell St at Victoria Rd
properties.publicTransport: Visit transportnsw.info to plan your trip.
properties.otherAdvice:
NRL: Eels v Broncos at Bankwest Stadium from 7:55pm until 9:40pm approx. 

Traffic may be heavier than usual on O'Connell St, Parramatta Rd, Church St, Victoria Rd and Pennant Hills Rd as fans travel to the stadium during Friday evening peak.

After the game, as fans leave the stadium and nearby carparks in Parramatta CBD traffic may also be heavy on local roads so allow extra travel time.

Fans driving to game should allow additional time for parking.

Traffic may be heavier than usual in both directions on the Princes Hwy approaching Kogarah as fans travel to and from the stadium.

Fans driving to the game should allow extra time for parking and be aware of increased pedestrian activity on local roads.
